    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-03-16T07:29:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-03-16T07:29:00-05:00" n="658"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">837.00/2036: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-16T07:00:00-05:29">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1921—7 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>43. Department’s policy to leave undisturbed results of November elections where
                    the issue of their validity was not raised before the courts, or where their
                    validity was declared by the courts, and to surround with adequate safeguards
                    partial elections to be held in those places where the courts have decreed
                    invalidity—and in this way compel the Cuban people to respect results obtained
                    under the law which they themselves had duly enacted, as construed by their own
                    courts—has I think been faithfully carried out. I am of the opinion therefore
                    that the results obtained yesterday, notwithstanding withdrawal of Liberals, may
                    be ratified.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Crowder</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
